{"title_page": "Miha Cimperman", "text_new": "{{Hatnote|For other possible meanings see [[Subject's last name (disambiguation)]]}} <!-- For subjects with only a single name, use if necessary. -->\n\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Miha Cimperman\n| image             = Miha Cimperman.jpg\n| alt               = Head of man\n| caption           = <!--(not needed as image is straightforward portrait)-->\n| birth_date        = {{birth date|1980|11|6|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[Ljubljana]], Slovenia\n| residence         = {{Unbulleted list |Slovenia}}\n| nationality       = [[Slovenian nationality|Slovenian]]\n| fields            = [[Data Science]] ([[Artificial Intelligence|Telemedicine| R&D&I]])\n| workplaces        = {{Unbulleted list |[[University of Ljubljana|Faculty of Economics]]|[[Jozef Stefan Institute]]}}\n| alma_mater        = {{Unbulleted list |[[University of Ljubljana]]}}\n| known_for         = [[Telemedicine |Technology Innovation]]\n| awards            = {{smaller|2012{{nbsp|2}}}}[[Best Paper Award in Telemedicine by ATA]]\n}}\n\n'''Miha Cimperman''' (born November 6, 1980) is a [[data scientist]], [[investor]], and [[philanthropist]]. He is a Lead [[Data Scientist]] at [https://www.ijs.si/ijsw/Artificial%20Intelligence%20E3 Artificial Intelligence Lab] at [https://www.ijs.si/ijsw/V001/JSI Jozef Stefan Institute] in [[Slovenia]].\n\n==Biography==\n===Early life and education===\nCimperman was born  (on 6 November 1980) and grew up in [[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]]. He is the second of four children of medical doctor Jo\u017ee Cimperman<ref> [http://zdravniki.org/joze-cimperman \"Listed medical doctor Joze Cimperman at University Medical Center, Department of Infectious Diseases in Ljubljana\"], \u201cUKC Ljubljana\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020. </ref> and Tatjana (n\u00e9e Kranjec). He developed an interest in business and investing in his youth. Cimperman speaks English, German, Slovenian, Croatian, Serbian and Russian.\n\nAfter receiving a BSc(H) degree in Electrical Engineering (specialized in [[Power Engineering]]) at [http://www.fe.uni-lj.si/en/ Faculty of Electrical Engineering, Ljubljana] in 2007<ref> Miha Cimperman, [https://plus.si.cobiss.net/opac7/bib/6128980 \"BSc(H) Thesis in Electrical Engineering: Krmiljenje odjema dobavitelja elektri\u010dne energije\"], \u201cFaculty of Electrical Engineering, Ljubljana\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020.</ref> and a doctorate in Consumer Behaviour Analytics in 2014 from the Faculty of Economics in Ljubljana, Slovenia<ref> Miha Cimperman, [https://plus.si.cobiss.net/opac7/bib/22014438 \"PhD Dissertation in Consumer Behaviour Analytics: Key determinats of the adoption of telemedicine - based services for elderly population\"], \u201cFaculty of Economics, Ljubljana\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020.</ref>, he became a researcher at Faculty of Economics, Ljubljana. Much of his early research focused on telemedicine and innovative technologies. Soon after he began various business partnerships and  created own company Zinter, Inc in 2008.<ref> [https://www.bizi.si/ZINTER-D-O-O/ \"Company Zinter, Inc owned by Miha Cimperman listed in the Corporate Register\"], \u201cBizi.si\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020. </ref>.\n<br />\n===Career===\nCimperman gained experience in Energy Sector and Data Technologies. He was a development lead for Energy IoT at a leading ITC European provider for the digital transformation of the telecommunications, transport, public safety and energy industries. Cimperman has worked as a Project Lead at an [https://www.ijs.si/ijsw/Artificial%20Intelligence%20E3 Artificial Intilligence Lab] at Jozef Stefan Institute, Ljubljana where he is in a charge of a full stack development, from data pipeline setup, explanatory analysis and feature engineering, modelling and containerization & streaming data analytics, graph modelling, optimization and ontology. Further, he developed a blockchain solution with an Ethereum Smart Contract. Meanwhile, his company Zinter, Inc is engaged in Innovation R&D Management and ICT solutions. \n<br />\n\n==Research==\nCimperman earned PhD in Consumer Behaviour Analytics in 2014 from the [http://www.ef.uni-lj.si/en Faculty of Economics in Ljubljana], Slovenia<ref> Miha Cimperman, [https://plus.si.cobiss.net/opac7/bib/22014438 \"PhD Dissertation in Consumer Behaviour Analytics: Key determinats of the adoption of telemedicine - based services for elderly population\"]</ref>. In short, Cimperman engaged in a Technology Innovation Marketing focused on a predictive modeling of consumers' innovation adoption decision making. The main objective of his dissertation was to understand the process of how and why people engage into new concepts, services, technologies and how different psychological composites influence behavior and final decision making. Model developed enabled predicting consumers' adoption behavior for future, currently nonexistent technologies. The methodology developed also included developing measurement instrument, along with methods of causal effects integration and interventions development for innovation R&D and marketing. \n\nCimperman was awarded the Best Paper Award from the American Telemedicine Association in 2012. Cimperman presented a research paper \"Key Influential Factors in Acceptance of e-Health Services for the Elderly\" (Cimperman et al, 2012) at an American Telemedicine Association Seventeenth Annual International Meeting and Exposition at San Jose Convention in California in 2012<ref> Presenter and co-contributor Miha Cimperman, [https://www.liebertpub.com/doi/pdf/10.1089/tmj.2012.9994\"Key Infulential Factors in Acceptance of e-Health Services for the Elderly\"], \u201cThe American Telemedicine Association, San Jose Convention, California\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020.</ref>. Additionally, Cimperman gave extensive lectures in the field of Data Technologies, such as at ITMO University in Russia <ref> Nikolina, A. (December 27, 2019),[https://news.itmo.ru/en/science/it/news/9066\"Jozef Stephan Institute\u2019s Miha Cimperman on Data Forecasting in Rail and Energy Industries\"], \u201cITMO University, St. Petersburg, Russia\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020.</ref>.\n\n==Writings==\n*2016: (with Brencic & Trkman) ''Analyzing Older Users\u2019 Home Telehealth Services Acceptance Behavior\u2014Applying an Extended UTAUT Model'', [https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1386505616300338 International Journal of Medical Informatics].\n*2013: (with Brencic, Trkman & Stanonik) ''Older Adults' Perceptions of Home Telehealth Services'', [https://www.liebertpub.com/doi/abs/10.1089/tmj.2012.0272 Telemedicine and e-Health].\n*2013: ''Modeling the Process of Elderly Telemedicine Services Acceptance'', [https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Vera_Boronenko/publication/321683068_Why_Supporting_Instruments_of_the_Small_Busines_Act_are_not_Widely_Used_by_the_European_SMEs_The_Case_of_Latvia/links/5a2ab9fba6fdccfbbf850ead/Why-Supporting-Instruments-of-the-Small-Busines-Act-are-not-Widely-Used-by-the-European-SMEs-The-Case-of-Latvia.pdf#page=617 Economic Integrations, Competition and Cooperation].\n\n==References==\n<references />\n==External links==\n* [https://www.linkedin.com/in/mihacimperman/ Miha Cimperman], on [[Linkedin]]\n* [https://www.ijs.si/ijsw/V001/JSI Jozef Stefan Institute]\n\n[[Category:Living People]]\n[[Category:Scientist]]\n[[Category:Slovenian scientists]]\n[[Category:Artificial intelligence researchers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Hatnote|For other possible meanings see [[Subject's last name (disambiguation)]]}} <!-- For subjects with only a single name, use if necessary. -->\n\n{{Infobox scientist\n| name              = Miha Cimperman\n| image             = Miha Cimperman.jpg\n| alt               = Head of man\n| caption           = <!--(not needed as image is straightforward portrait)-->\n| birth_date        = {{birth date|1980|11|6|df=y}}\n| birth_place       = [[Ljubljana]], Slovenia\n| residence         = {{Unbulleted list |Slovenia}}\n| nationality       = [[Slovenian nationality|Slovenian]]\n| fields            = [[Data Science]] ([[Artificial Intelligence|Telemedicine| R&D&I]])\n| workplaces        = {{Unbulleted list |[[University of Ljubljana|Faculty of Economics]]|[[Jozef Stefan Institute]]}}\n| alma_mater        = {{Unbulleted list |[[University of Ljubljana]]}}\n| known_for         = [[Telemedicine |Technology Innovation]]\n| awards            = {{smaller|2012{{nbsp|2}}}}[[Best Paper Award in Telemedicine by ATA]]\n}}\n\n'''Miha Cimperman''' (born November 6, 1980) is a [[data scientist]], [[investor]], and [[philanthropist]]. He is a Lead [[Data Scientist]] at [https://www.ijs.si/ijsw/Artificial%20Intelligence%20E3 Artificial Intelligence Lab] at [https://www.ijs.si/ijsw/V001/JSI Jozef Stefan Institute] in [[Slovenia]].\n\n==Biography==\n===Early life and education===\nCimperman was born  (on 6 November 1980) and grew up in [[Ljubljana]], [[Slovenia]]. He is the second of four children of medical doctor Jo\u017ee Cimperman<ref> [http://zdravniki.org/joze-cimperman \"Listed medical doctor Joze Cimperman at University Medical Center, Department of Infectious Diseases in Ljubljana\"], \u201cUKC Ljubljana\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020. </ref> and Tatjana (n\u00e9e Kranjec). He developed an interest in business and investing in his youth. Cimperman speaks English, German, Slovenian, Croatian, Serbian and Russian.\n\nAfter receiving a BSc(H) degree in Electrical Engineering (specialized in [[Power Engineering]]) at [http://www.fe.uni-lj.si/en/ Faculty of Electrical Engineering, Ljubljana] in 2007<ref> Miha Cimperman, [https://plus.si.cobiss.net/opac7/bib/6128980 \"BSc(H) Thesis in Electrical Engineering: Krmiljenje odjema dobavitelja elektri\u010dne energije\"], \u201cFaculty of Electrical Engineering, Ljubljana\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020.</ref> and a doctorate in Consumer Behaviour Analytics in 2014 from the Faculty of Economics in Ljubljana, Slovenia<ref> Miha Cimperman, [https://plus.si.cobiss.net/opac7/bib/22014438 \"PhD Dissertation in Consumer Behaviour Analytics: Key determinats of the adoption of telemedicine - based services for elderly population\"], \u201cFaculty of Economics, Ljubljana\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020.</ref>, he became a researcher at Faculty of Economics, Ljubljana. Much of his early research focused on telemedicine and innovative technologies. Soon after he began various business partnerships and  created own company Zinter, Inc in 2008.<ref> [https://www.bizi.si/ZINTER-D-O-O/ \"Company Zinter, Inc owned by Miha Cimperman listed in the Corporate Register\"], \u201cBizi.si\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020. </ref>.\n<br />\n===Career===\nCimperman gained experience in Energy Sector and Data Technologies. He was a development lead for Energy IoT at a leading ITC European provider for the digital transformation of the telecommunications, transport, public safety and energy industries. Cimperman has worked as a Project Lead at an [https://www.ijs.si/ijsw/Artificial%20Intelligence%20E3 Artificial Intilligence Lab] at Jozef Stefan Institute, Ljubljana where he is in a charge of a full stack development, from data pipeline setup, explanatory analysis and feature engineering, modelling and containerization & streaming data analytics, graph modelling, optimization and ontology. Further, he developed a blockchain solution with an Ethereum Smart Contract. Meanwhile, his company Zinter, Inc is engaged in Innovation R&D Management and ICT solutions. \n<br />\n\n==Research==\nCimperman earned PhD in Consumer Behaviour Analytics in 2014 from the [http://www.ef.uni-lj.si/en Faculty of Economics in Ljubljana], Slovenia<ref> Miha Cimperman, [https://plus.si.cobiss.net/opac7/bib/22014438 \"PhD Dissertation in Consumer Behaviour Analytics: Key determinats of the adoption of telemedicine - based services for elderly population\"]</ref>. In short, Cimperman engaged in a Technology Innovation Marketing focused on a predictive modeling of consumers' innovation adoption decision making. The main objective of his dissertation was to understand the process of how and why people engage into new concepts, services, technologies and how different psychological composites influence behavior and final decision making. Model developed enabled predicting consumers' adoption behavior for future, currently nonexistent technologies. The methodology developed also included developing measurement instrument, along with methods of causal effects integration and interventions development for innovation R&D and marketing. \n\nCimperman was awarded the Best Paper Award from the American Telemedicine Association in 2012. Cimperman presented a research paper \"Key Influential Factors in Acceptance of e-Health Services for the Elderly\" (Cimperman et al, 2012) at an American Telemedicine Association Seventeenth Annual International Meeting and Exposition at San Jose Convention in California in 2012<ref> Presenter and co-contributor Miha Cimperman, [https://www.liebertpub.com/doi/pdf/10.1089/tmj.2012.9994\"Key Infulential Factors in Acceptance of e-Health Services for the Elderly\"], \u201cThe American Telemedicine Association, San Jose Convention, California\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020.</ref>. Additionally, Cimperman gave extensive lectures in the field of Data Technologies, such as at ITMO University in Russia <ref> Nikolina, A. (December 27, 2019),[https://news.itmo.ru/en/science/it/news/9066\"Jozef Stephan Institute\u2019s Miha Cimperman on Data Forecasting in Rail and Energy Industries\"], \u201cITMO University, St. Petersburg, Russia\u201d. Retrieved April 10, 2020.</ref>.\n\n==Writings==\n*2016: (with Brencic & Trkman) ''Analyzing Older Users\u2019 Home Telehealth Services Acceptance Behavior\u2014Applying an Extended UTAUT Model'', [https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S1386505616300338 International Journal of Medical Informatics].\n*2013: (with Brencic, Trkman & Stanonik) ''Older Adults' Perceptions of Home Telehealth Services'', [https://www.liebertpub.com/doi/abs/10.1089/tmj.2012.0272 Telemedicine and e-Health].\n*2013: ''Modeling the Process of Elderly Telemedicine Services Acceptance'', [https://www.researchgate.net/profile/Vera_Boronenko/publication/321683068_Why_Supporting_Instruments_of_the_Small_Busines_Act_are_not_Widely_Used_by_the_European_SMEs_The_Case_of_Latvia/links/5a2ab9fba6fdccfbbf850ead/Why-Supporting-Instruments-of-the-Small-Busines-Act-are-not-Widely-Used-by-the-European-SMEs-The-Case-of-Latvia.pdf#page=617 Economic Integrations, Competition and Cooperation].\n\n==References==\n<references />\n==External links==\n* [https://www.linkedin.com/in/mihacimperman/ Miha Cimperman], on [[Linkedin]]\n* [https://www.ijs.si/ijsw/V001/JSI Jozef Stefan Institute]\n<br />\n{{[[Category:Living People]][[Category:Scientist]][[Category:Slovenian scientists]][[Category:Artificial intelligence researchers]]}}\n", "name_user": "Herminapan", "label": "safe", "comment": "Managed external link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miha_Cimperman"}
